Distribution
------------

   You may not make a profit from distributing Guidemaster.  You may not put
it in a disk collection without prior permission from the author.  Specific
exceptions are as follows:  Any collection from Fred Fish, any official
archive of the Aminet collection.

   You may not modify or eliminate files from the archive; you may split the
archive if convenient so long as all the files are still available on the
distribution medium.

   Certain parts of the package may be distributed separately, subject to
agreement with the following requirements:

   The "Guidemaster" main program may be included in any disk collection, or
with any product that is freely distributable, for use as the viewer of
(compressed) Amigaguide files.  You must include somewhere in your
documentation the following copyright notice:

   Guidemaster.  (C) 1995 Greywire designs.  All Rights Reserved.
Reproduced and distributed under license from Greywire designs.

   If you are a disk distributer, or are distributing a commercial package,
please contact the author and arrange to receive a license and the latest
version.

   The shareware registration fee is $10.  You will recieve the latest
version on disk, and possibly a printed manual if there is any demand for
it.

About
-----

   This software is developed on an Amiga 500, with an 85MB hd and 4.5MB
ram.  The documentation is created with a combination of Makeinfo and TeX /
Metafont.  Printed manuals, if requested, will be printed on a Canon BJ-200
printer.


